  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Poverty Alleviation Project in Northeast of Sichuan Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the mountainous areas in Northeast of Sichuan Province, poverty is a way of life for many of the farm families. This project will assist 240 farm families in the area, providing a total of 2,000 goats, 140 sows and 7000 geese. Self-help groups have been formed in the three project communities of the targeted underdeveloped villages as part of Heifer Values-Based Holistic Community Development model.  This will provide participants with training in group management, livestock production management and environmental protection, as well as the Heifer Cornerstones and gender justice. At least one participant from each self-help group will be trained as a village animal health worker. The project will not only increase the income of the communities, but also the participants&#x2019; organizational capacity by strengthening cooperation, developing and understanding co-development and fostering joint problem-solving. Another 480 families will benefit through &#x201C;passing on the gift&#x201D; within five years.</narrative>
  </description>
